34. READCONF.EXE, version 3.0
    
    READCONF.EXE is used instead of READCONF.COM (version 1.0 & 2.0)
    for the multiple configurations in AUTOEXEC.BAT.

    It reads a file: AUTOCONF.DAT is created by AUTOCONF.SYS on bootup
    and contains the chosen configuration letter. READCONF defines   
    a variable in the permanent master DOS environment:
    CONF=x , ex: CONF=C for the configuration C.

    Note: option /B of AUTOCONF.SYS was removed.

    If the environment size is to large, a message occurs.
    If READCONF does not find AUTOCONF.DAT an error occurs.
    
    Note: syntax  for READCONF: "READCONF X"
    where X is your boot drive (C is default)
    It is usefull for those who use SWAPING with STACKER of other programms.

    You just have to take the variable  CONF further in AUTOEXEC.BAT:   
    if %conf%=="A" goto ConfigA   ;see manual of DOS
    ...

    Note: it is no longer 1 for configuratio A, but A --> you can make
    configurations easilly for any ASCII code.

