86.     Concerning: Chicago, DOS and QEMM 7.X DOSDATA
        During the bootup:

        -> Chicago: Windows 4.0 does not need QEMM, it is totally absurd to
                    use it with Chicago, since it can only cause problems.
        -> DOS    : You have two types of configurations, one with and another
                    without DOSDATA. When you bootup your computer, you have
                    to press F4 key in order to boot with MS-DOS. Then you
                    choose a configuration with AUTOCONF, which contains 
                    DOSDATA. The message Loading Windows (or something like
                    that) is shown. Since DOSDATA reruns the CONFIG.SYS you 
                    are forced to press F4 again to run MS-DOS.

                    With option /O:

                    The last procedure is supressed with this version of
                    AUTOCONF. The last press on the F4 key is done by AUTOCONF
                    itself. You bootup with DOSDATA is as simple as before,
                    like without Chicago: F4 + Configuration.

        Note: some older bios will not support this function.            

        Note: the F4 key is simulated in any case, except when you want to
              run Chicago. If DOSDATA is not present, a beep will occur at 
              the end of the bootup, since the computer keeps the "pressed"
              key until the DOS prompt.

              CLRBUF small utility will suppress this beep. See the help file
              for details.

